1. Introduction
The objective of Task 1 is to perform an exploratory data analysis (EDA) of historical Brent crude oil prices in order to understand long-term trends, volatility patterns, and the relationship between major global events and oil price movements. This initial analysis provides the foundation for later change point detection and modeling tasks.
2. Data Description
2.1 Brent Oil Price Data
â€¢	Dataset: BrentOilPrices.csv
â€¢	Frequency: Daily
â€¢	Key variables:
o	Date
o	Brent crude oil price (USD per barrel)
The dataset spans multiple years and captures periods of market stability, sharp price shocks, and high volatility.
2.2 Event Data
A structured event dataset was created to capture major geopolitical, economic, and oil-market-related events that could influence Brent oil prices. This dataset is stored as a CSV file for easy integration with the price data.
